      "span_text": "However, compounds 6c and 6d, possessing a substituted thienyl group at R 1 and a carboxymethyl group at second position of pyrimidine ring, showed more than a 25-fold selectivity towards PDE4B. Further modification of the above compounds resulted in compounds 7a-d (Figure 2 ), which showed potent inhibitory activity on PDE4B (pIC   nM, 6.8 nM, and 15 nM, respectively) and >100-fold selectivity over PDE4D (PDE4B pIC 50 1700 nM, 2900 nM, 3100 nM, respectively)."
